-- Lafarge Nigeria unit says 2013 pretax up 30 pct, pays 3.3 naira dividend
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Thu Mar 20, 2014 07:35AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, March 20 (Reuters) - Lafarge's <LAFP.PA> Nigerian unit Wapco <WAPCO.LG> said on Thursday its 2013 full-year pretax profit rose 30.3 percent to 27.71 billion naira ($168.3 million).

The local unit of the world's largest cement producer also said in a filing with the Nigerian Stock Exchange revenue jumped to 98.79 billion naira from 87.76 billion the previous year.